714. fors ..] ‘chance and valour are confounded in one.' The phrase seems to mark the fury of the eombatants, who, disdaining caution, dash together in a. melec in which it looks as if chance alone could decide the issue. Any one, who has seen two boxers drop scientific sparring and really set to, will understand the idea which Virgil wishes to suggest.
